# MathScript Frontend Rules

## Stack
React 18, Vite, GSAP 3, vanilla CSS-in-JS (inline styles), no TypeScript, no Redux.

## File Conventions
- All API calls go through `frontend/src/api/client.js` — never call `fetch()` directly in a component
- Add new API functions to `client.js` following the existing async/await pattern
- New pages go in `frontend/src/pages/`
- New reusable components go in `frontend/src/components/`
- Utility functions go in `frontend/src/utils/`

## State Management
- Use `useState` and `useCallback` — do not introduce Redux, Zustand, or Context API
- Session ID lives in `localStorage` under key `mathscript_session_id`
- Session must match pattern `/^sess_[a-z0-9]{6,20}$/` before being used
- App routing is a state machine in `App.jsx` — add new screens as new `screen` values

## GSAP Animations
- Always clean up GSAP with `gsap.context(() => { ... }).revert()` in the useEffect cleanup
- Use refs for animation targets — never use class/id selectors in GSAP
- Wrap GSAP imports in try/catch if you're conditionally loading

## Error Handling
- Always check if API response exists before accessing `.field`: `const data = await fn(); if (!data) return;`
- Wrap fetch calls in try/catch with user-visible error state (not console.log)
- Show fallback UI when images fail to load (use `onError` on `<img>`)

## Performance
- Images from Gemini come as base64 data URIs — do not store large images in state longer than needed
- Lazy-load heavy components (MiniGame, AnimatedScene) if added to new routes
- Use `useCallback` for functions passed as props to prevent re-renders

## Common Bugs to Avoid
- Forgetting `key` prop in list renders
- Setting state inside an unmounted component (add `isMounted` ref or use AbortController)
- GSAP timeline not being killed after component unmounts (memory leak)
- Calling `generateStory()` with undefined `sessionId` — guard with early return
